						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Chōḻa, Rājakēsarivarmaṉ (Āditya I), Year 25 = 896 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This registers a gift of 30 cows for the maintenance of a perpetual lamp in the temple by Sembiyan Maḻanāṭṭu-vēḷāṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Koṟṟaṉ Māṟan of Kākaikaḷūr in Kilāl-kuṟuviḍam. This gift was left in charge of the <hi rend="italic">mulapariḍai.</hi> The high regnal, Year of king and the early script of the inscription make it attribute to Aditya I.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi> Vol. XIII No. 313.]</p>						

						</summary>
